  "texts": [
    "Similar to single-cell transcriptomic data, spatial omics datasets generated in different batches also contain batch-specific systematic variations that present a challenge to batch-effect removal and data integration.",
    "In our study, we demonstrated that by combining SEDR and Harmony, we were able to effectively remove batch effects present.Spatial omics technologies such as Stereo-seq are able to measure a large number of spots in a single experiment through high spatial resolutions and large tissue sizes.",
    "Based on current trends, we expect to see ever-increasing throughput from spatial omics experiments, which will result in spatial omics big data that poses significant challenges to data analysis and integration.",
    "Computational methods that employ GCNs require the entire graph to be loaded into GPU memory, which inhibits their application to very large datasets.",
    "Currently, the current version of SEDR is the most CPU and GPU memory efficient and second fastest among methods that do not employ image processing."
